   <abstract displayLabel="Description">Thomas writes to his sister from Fort Griffin (Tex.) about: his having been in transit; his condolences on the death of George; meeting a survey crew on the way to the Fort; crop failures the past three years</abstract>
   <note type="content">Fort Griffin served as one in a line of western defensive forts in the north portion of West Texas from 1867 to 1881. It provided settlers protection from early Comanche and Kiowa raids</note>
